1
00:00:32,198 --> 00:00:36,953
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

2
00:00:37,036 --> 00:00:38,829
- Hello, nice to meet you.
- Hi.

3
00:00:38,913 --> 00:00:40,081
- Nice to meet you.
- Looking forward to meeting you.

4
00:00:40,164 --> 00:00:41,999
- Is this Ms. Lee?
- Hey.

5
00:00:48,339 --> 00:00:49,423
Are you okay?

6
00:00:50,550 --> 00:00:51,717
Are you hurt?

7
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:53,844
- Hello.
- Ms. Ui-yeong?

8
00:00:53,928 --> 00:00:55,137
- A friend...
- Looking for a date?

9
00:00:55,221 --> 00:00:58,266
Are they all asking me out
on a blind date?

10
00:01:00,643 --> 00:01:02,770
- What in the world is going on?
- Exactly.

11
00:01:03,771 --> 00:01:04,772
Sorry?

12
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:09,610
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE
EPISODE 3

13
00:01:12,238 --> 00:01:13,364
Have I been hacked?

14
00:01:13,698 --> 00:01:15,825
Has my number been leaked?
From my phone company?

15
00:01:15,908 --> 00:01:17,076
Maybe from online shopping?

16
00:01:17,535 --> 00:01:19,453
YOON BAK:
HELLO, NICE TO MEET YOU. I'M YOON BAK

17
00:01:19,537 --> 00:01:21,831
- Hello, nice to meet you. I'm Yoon Bak.
- Who is this?

18
00:01:22,498 --> 00:01:24,083
I'M YUK JUN-SEO

19
00:01:24,166 --> 00:01:25,501
I'm Yuk Jun-seo.

20
00:01:25,585 --> 00:01:28,337
I'm Lee Ho-gwang.
I'm a singer and stage performer.

21
00:01:28,421 --> 00:01:29,839
When are you free this week?

22
00:01:29,922 --> 00:01:31,007
Hello, Ui-yeong.

23
00:01:31,090 --> 00:01:33,759
I'm Kim Do-yun,
the brother of your dermatologist.

24
00:01:33,843 --> 00:01:34,844
What's going on?

25
00:01:34,927 --> 00:01:37,305
Hello, I'm Song Ji-hun, Na-hyeon's friend.

26
00:01:37,388 --> 00:01:39,265
I sent him your photo,
and he's interested.

27
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:40,975
He's super successful as a teacher.

28
00:01:41,183 --> 00:01:42,935
- I'll give him your number.
- Wait!

29
00:01:43,603 --> 00:01:44,729
I'll see who I know.

30
00:01:44,812 --> 00:01:46,188
I gave your number to a friend.

31
00:01:46,272 --> 00:01:47,690
- Random, but sure.
- I'll share your number.

32
00:01:47,773 --> 00:01:49,650
Okay, I'll look into it.

33
00:01:53,237 --> 00:01:54,989
LEE DA-EUN FROM CLASS OF 2013

34
00:01:56,490 --> 00:01:57,950
YOU KNOW A GOOD GUY? I'M SO LONELY

35
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:00,703
CAN YOU SET ME UP WITH A GUY?

36
00:02:00,786 --> 00:02:02,079
CAN YOU FIND ME A BOYFRIEND?

37
00:02:04,081 --> 00:02:05,791
PASTE

38
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:07,793
FIND A GUY FOR ME! YOU KNOW ANYONE NICE?

39
00:02:14,133 --> 00:02:16,636
You've got to be kidding me!

40
00:02:18,429 --> 00:02:19,930
You're crazy!

41
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:26,520
- I'm home.
- Hey.

42
00:02:28,397 --> 00:02:30,024
- Gosh, my shoulders.
- Oh, man.

43
00:02:30,816 --> 00:02:32,026
Hey

44
00:02:35,363 --> 00:02:36,947
what's all this?

45
00:02:37,615 --> 00:02:40,368
I thought you liked
wearing your uniform to work every day.

46
00:02:41,285 --> 00:02:42,370
Are you not feeling well?

47
00:02:43,579 --> 00:02:45,414
You don't have a fever.

48
00:02:45,498 --> 00:02:47,708
Stop it. That's not it.

49
00:02:47,792 --> 00:02:49,710
Next time I'm drunk,
just turn my phone off.

50
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:51,003
Or chop my hands off.

51
00:02:51,087 --> 00:02:53,047
- Not your credit card?
- Hey.

52
00:02:53,130 --> 00:02:55,633
They're not just any clothes.
They're my armor.

53
00:02:56,092 --> 00:02:58,386
Come on. Look at this.

54
00:02:58,761 --> 00:03:01,889
What armor is this soft and fluffy?

55
00:03:02,223 --> 00:03:04,392
What about this?

56
00:03:04,892 --> 00:03:06,227
Is this camouflage cream?

57
00:03:07,269 --> 00:03:09,855
- My goodness.
- You'd better not use any.

58
00:03:10,439 --> 00:03:11,565
It's all mine.

59
00:03:12,483 --> 00:03:13,693
Geez.

60
00:03:17,738 --> 00:03:20,866
This hides my flaws
and makes me feel confident.

61
00:03:21,283 --> 00:03:22,410
I'd say that's an armor.

62
00:03:26,414 --> 00:03:27,415
Alright.

63
00:03:39,051 --> 00:03:41,095
It may have been a drunken wish

64
00:03:41,303 --> 00:03:42,847
but a chance is a chance.

65
00:03:47,226 --> 00:03:49,562
There's only a 1% chance now

66
00:03:49,937 --> 00:03:52,440
but I'll get to know them
and find my best match.

67
00:03:53,149 --> 00:03:54,817
I'LL GIVE YOUR NUMBER TO HIM

68
00:03:55,067 --> 00:03:56,360
OH, GOSH... I'LL LOOK FOR ONE

69
00:03:56,444 --> 00:03:59,280
- I'll look for one.
- Even your texts sound drunk.

70
00:03:59,363 --> 00:04:00,614
- Let's grab lunch sometime.
- Random

71
00:04:00,698 --> 00:04:02,241
- but sure.
- Ui-yeong, are you drunk?

72
00:04:02,324 --> 00:04:03,868
If I knew a good guy,
I wouldn't be single.

73
00:04:03,951 --> 00:04:06,162
- Do you know anyone?
- Those are just empty words.

74
00:04:06,579 --> 00:04:07,580
I'll look for one.

75
00:04:07,663 --> 00:04:09,248
Can I ask you a favor, too?

76
00:04:09,331 --> 00:04:11,834
Can you book a wedding consultation
at your hotel?

77
00:04:11,917 --> 00:04:14,378
Of course, it's all about give and take.

78
00:04:14,962 --> 00:04:17,339
Of course. When's a good time for you?

79
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:21,218
HELLO, NICE TO MEET YOU. I'M YOON BAK

80
00:04:21,302 --> 00:04:23,304
Hello, I'm Lee Ui-yeong.

81
00:04:23,763 --> 00:04:25,639
Are you free this Saturday?

82
00:04:27,516 --> 00:04:28,559
Alright, then.

83
00:04:28,642 --> 00:04:29,894
YOON BAK, 37, AT 1:30 P.M.

84
00:04:29,977 --> 00:04:32,313
MATH INSTRUCTOR

85
00:04:33,022 --> 00:04:34,315
YOON BAK, 37, MATH INSTRUCTOR,
AT 1:30 P.M.

86
00:04:38,694 --> 00:04:40,613
Good morning.

87
00:04:42,656 --> 00:04:44,492
Is the other one for me?

88
00:04:44,575 --> 00:04:47,787
No, they're both mine. I need to wake up.

89
00:04:47,953 --> 00:04:49,580
Hmm? Did you not sleep well?

90
00:04:50,372 --> 00:04:51,373
You look great to me.

91
00:04:53,292 --> 00:04:54,835
Your calendar is so full!

92
00:04:56,879 --> 00:04:58,672
They're all blind dates!

93
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:00,174
KIM DO-HA, 38, SONGWRITER, AT 7 P.M.

94
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:03,677
LEE SEONG-JAE, 31, DESIGNER,
AT 7:30 A.M.

95
00:05:03,761 --> 00:05:05,971
People go on blind dates before work?

96
00:05:06,055 --> 00:05:07,556
Yeah, I'm one of them.

97
00:05:08,390 --> 00:05:10,226
There was no other time. I had no choice.

98
00:05:12,186 --> 00:05:15,856
I was just determined to fix
what I'd done last night

99
00:05:15,940 --> 00:05:17,399
but this is going too far, right?

100
00:05:17,483 --> 00:05:18,651
Seeing just one is tiring.

101
00:05:18,734 --> 00:05:20,611
And this isn't even polite, right?

102
00:05:21,779 --> 00:05:23,697
You're not even dating anyone yet.

103
00:05:23,781 --> 00:05:26,826
It's not rude,
as long as you do your best on every date.

104
00:05:27,618 --> 00:05:29,662
Don't worry. Just go for it.

105
00:05:29,912 --> 00:05:32,832
Most importantly, if you cancel now

106
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:35,292
people won't set you up.

107
00:05:35,376 --> 00:05:37,378
That's one less matchmaker you'll have.

108
00:05:39,755 --> 00:05:41,048
That can't happen.

109
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,681
DEERFIDDICH, PREMIUM WHISKEY BRAND

110
00:05:48,764 --> 00:05:53,936
Our hotel is hosting
the 100th anniversary event

111
00:05:54,019 --> 00:05:56,230
for Deerfiddich
from the middle of next month.

112
00:05:58,399 --> 00:06:00,359
A big project now, of all times?

113
00:06:00,442 --> 00:06:01,777
The event is three weeks long?

114
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:03,654
Yes, we'll set up a pop-up store

115
00:06:03,737 --> 00:06:07,700
to display the whiskey
and hold tasting sessions in the lobby.

116
00:06:07,783 --> 00:06:11,662
The brand has asked us
to plan and organize all of it.

117
00:06:11,745 --> 00:06:12,913
- I see.
- I see.

118
00:06:13,831 --> 00:06:16,375
Why don't we use temporary walls

119
00:06:16,458 --> 00:06:18,460
to create a "shop-in-shop" style setup?

120
00:06:18,586 --> 00:06:20,713
We could put up a sign
and hire a bartender

121
00:06:20,796 --> 00:06:22,631
to create a Scottish-style whiskey bar

122
00:06:22,715 --> 00:06:24,466
in our hotel lobby.

123
00:06:24,717 --> 00:06:25,718
That's a great idea.

124
00:06:25,801 --> 00:06:27,720
We'll develop that idea.

125
00:06:27,803 --> 00:06:29,847
Purchasing, please look for a company

126
00:06:29,930 --> 00:06:31,473
- that could set up the shop.
- Okay.

127
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:34,018
Facilities, please help us
when we set up the shop.

128
00:06:34,101 --> 00:06:35,769
Yes, you can leave that to us.

129
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,314
Can we have a glass, too?

130
00:06:54,246 --> 00:06:55,247
Please.

131
00:06:58,375 --> 00:07:03,339
PURCHASING TEAM OFFICE

132
00:07:09,511 --> 00:07:12,431
You know
how Ui-yeong's been working nonstop?

133
00:07:12,681 --> 00:07:14,975
She's been there to solve every issue.

134
00:07:15,059 --> 00:07:16,101
Yes.

135
00:07:16,185 --> 00:07:18,729
So, let her live her life now.

136
00:07:18,812 --> 00:07:20,689
We can manage with what we've learned.

137
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:23,233
You should prove yourself
before the internship's over.

138
00:07:23,317 --> 00:07:25,569
Yes, I'm ready to work really hard.

139
00:07:26,362 --> 00:07:27,363
Right on!

140
00:07:29,073 --> 00:07:30,074
- Here.
- Thank you.

141
00:07:32,743 --> 00:07:35,245
Sae-byeok, are you free tonight?

142
00:07:35,371 --> 00:07:36,664
- Can we talk?
- Alright!

143
00:07:37,539 --> 00:07:39,667
Should we look for designers after dinner?

144
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:41,543
- Yes!
- Alright, cheers.

145
00:07:55,140 --> 00:07:56,183
You look great.

146
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:01,939
Looks delicious.

147
00:08:05,234 --> 00:08:06,527
What do you do for a living?

148
00:08:11,323 --> 00:08:13,158
I learned from the countless first dates

149
00:08:13,492 --> 00:08:16,745
that the world is big,
and everyone's so different.

150
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:18,580
None of the guys I met were

151
00:08:18,831 --> 00:08:21,792
even slightly similar.

152
00:08:22,334 --> 00:08:24,336
Everyone was

153
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:26,714
- a universe like no other.
- Nice to meet you.

154
00:08:26,797 --> 00:08:28,841
You know me, right? I'm Yoon Bak.

155
00:08:28,924 --> 00:08:32,011
YOON BAK, 37, STAR MATH INSTRUCTOR

156
00:08:38,475 --> 00:08:39,727
You're already done eating.

157
00:08:39,810 --> 00:08:41,520
Would you like another soup?

158
00:08:41,603 --> 00:08:43,063
Are you already taking care of me?

159
00:08:43,147 --> 00:08:44,314
That was unexpected.

160
00:08:45,024 --> 00:08:46,025
Sorry?

161
00:08:46,108 --> 00:08:47,192
Just kidding.

162
00:08:47,317 --> 00:08:49,236
I usually eat my meals in a meeting

163
00:08:49,319 --> 00:08:50,612
so I always eat fast.

164
00:08:51,071 --> 00:08:53,282
I see.

165
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,325
You must be so busy.

166
00:08:55,409 --> 00:08:57,911
I hear your classes are so popular.

167
00:08:57,995 --> 00:08:59,913
Is that what you really want to know?

168
00:08:59,997 --> 00:09:01,582
Aren't you just wondering

169
00:09:01,665 --> 00:09:04,043
if I'll have time to date
and take care of you?

170
00:09:04,126 --> 00:09:05,419
Oh, well...

171
00:09:07,713 --> 00:09:09,548
Do you have time?

172
00:09:09,715 --> 00:09:11,341
Time is gold to me.

173
00:09:11,425 --> 00:09:13,510
It must be at least silver or bronze
to you, too.

174
00:09:13,594 --> 00:09:15,846
We're here to meet
and listen to each other

175
00:09:15,929 --> 00:09:18,140
so what do you think happens next?

176
00:09:20,768 --> 00:09:22,019
What's going to happen?

177
00:09:23,270 --> 00:09:24,897
We know how it'll go.

178
00:09:25,939 --> 00:09:28,275
- You can be my girlfriend.
- What?

179
00:09:28,358 --> 00:09:30,569
If you just want to date,
I'll be a boyfriend.

180
00:09:30,652 --> 00:09:32,613
If you want to get married,
I'll be a husband.

181
00:09:32,696 --> 00:09:34,239
No need to think about anything.

182
00:09:34,323 --> 00:09:36,158
Just use me. I'll let you.

183
00:09:36,784 --> 00:09:38,619
That's what this is about. It's simple.

184
00:09:38,702 --> 00:09:41,747
He flirts like he's lecturing
a high school senior.

185
00:09:41,830 --> 00:09:44,458
I hear you love to work out.

186
00:09:44,541 --> 00:09:46,001
Are you okay with eating carbs?

187
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:49,171
Yes, I prefer eating more of it
to fuel my workouts.

188
00:09:49,254 --> 00:09:51,632
YUK JUN-SEO, 29, FORMER UDT MEMBER
AND REHAB TRAINER

189
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:52,925
I see.

190
00:09:53,884 --> 00:09:57,096
What's your priority in a relationship?

191
00:09:57,179 --> 00:09:58,263
Eating.

192
00:09:58,347 --> 00:10:00,140
Having different tastes is noticeable

193
00:10:00,224 --> 00:10:01,600
at every meal.

194
00:10:02,267 --> 00:10:04,144
Do you like to eat?

195
00:10:04,353 --> 00:10:06,980
Yes, I love to eat. I'm not picky, either.

196
00:10:08,315 --> 00:10:10,442
I have so many restaurants
I want to check out.

197
00:10:10,651 --> 00:10:12,945
We could even go to a few today.

198
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:14,404
This is exciting.

199
00:10:15,614 --> 00:10:16,949
"A few"?

200
00:10:21,912 --> 00:10:22,913
Tacos!

201
00:10:32,923 --> 00:10:33,924
Bagels!

202
00:10:35,175 --> 00:10:36,176
Gelato!

203
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:39,763
Desserts!

204
00:10:47,771 --> 00:10:51,483
I feel like my stomach will explode
if I see him again.

205
00:11:01,493 --> 00:11:04,246
I was going to pay for the coffee.

206
00:11:04,329 --> 00:11:07,624
Don't say that

207
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:10,127
LEE HO-GWANG, 36, MUSICAL ACTOR

208
00:11:10,752 --> 00:11:15,424
You gave me the greatest gift,
a pricelessly perfect day.

209
00:11:15,841 --> 00:11:17,092
You're my muse

210
00:11:18,677 --> 00:11:19,803
from today on.

211
00:11:21,430 --> 00:11:22,431
Your muse?

212
00:11:22,514 --> 00:11:25,517
Like Christine
in "The Phantom of the Opera."

213
00:11:26,268 --> 00:11:27,477
"The Phantom of the Opera"?

214
00:11:29,021 --> 00:11:32,900
Ho-gwang, it's getting late.
I'd better get home.

215
00:11:32,983 --> 00:11:34,693
I live right here, so I can go alone.

216
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:37,196
No

217
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:40,240
I don't want you to walk alone
in the dark.

218
00:11:41,158 --> 00:11:42,951
I can already sense the dark souls

219
00:11:43,410 --> 00:11:45,287
trying to steal you away, my sunshine.

220
00:11:45,370 --> 00:11:49,208
The man who called me his muse,
Christine, and sunshine

221
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:50,584
and got overly protective...

222
00:11:50,667 --> 00:11:51,960
She told you to go. Leave.

223
00:11:52,044 --> 00:11:54,463
She doesn't seem to want to show you
where she lives.

224
00:11:54,546 --> 00:11:57,299
Who are you, ma'am?

225
00:11:57,382 --> 00:11:58,884
Why are you intruding?

226
00:11:58,967 --> 00:12:00,636
Me? Her mom.

227
00:12:00,802 --> 00:12:03,722
Jesus Christ Superstar!

228
00:12:03,847 --> 00:12:05,766
No, not a superstar. Her mom.

229
00:12:05,849 --> 00:12:08,060
It's like you're not even listening.

230
00:12:08,143 --> 00:12:11,396
He was tragically defeated
by the nemesis of romance.

231
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:13,607
Mother

232
00:12:13,732 --> 00:12:15,067
My mother

233
00:12:15,150 --> 00:12:17,527
Your mother

234
00:12:25,911 --> 00:12:30,624
Please join me in prayer
to give thanks for our date.

235
00:12:30,707 --> 00:12:33,877
This man doesn't go on dates on Sundays
because that's the Lord's day.

236
00:12:33,961 --> 00:12:35,337
Do you also like drinking?

237
00:12:35,420 --> 00:12:36,964
Why can't you just drink at home?

238
00:12:37,047 --> 00:12:39,049
Why do women have to go out for drinks?

239
00:12:39,132 --> 00:12:42,052
This one still seemed
like he wasn't over his ex.

240
00:12:43,011 --> 00:12:44,972
Sure, you can have different tastes.

241
00:12:45,055 --> 00:12:48,183
But why would you pour the sauce
without asking the other person first?

242
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:49,977
That says a lot about who you are.

243
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:53,480
A man who can't stand inconsiderate people
who pour the sauce without asking.

244
00:12:53,563 --> 00:12:55,148
- Please be my girlfriend!
- Please be my girlfriend!

245
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:56,775
- Please.
- Please be my girlfriend.

246
00:12:56,858 --> 00:12:57,901
- Please!
- Please!

247
00:12:57,985 --> 00:13:00,362
The problem is, among all those men

248
00:13:00,779 --> 00:13:02,864
none of them were my type.

249
00:13:20,465 --> 00:13:22,884
Ui-yeong!

250
00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:24,803
Where are you going?

251
00:13:24,886 --> 00:13:27,889
Ui-yeong! I love you!

252
00:13:28,223 --> 00:13:30,017
Stop right there!

253
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:31,310
- Ui-yeong!
- Ui-yeong!

254
00:13:31,393 --> 00:13:32,477
Ui-yeong!

255
00:13:45,949 --> 00:13:48,452
I said you passed as my girlfriend
because I like you.

256
00:13:48,535 --> 00:13:50,287
Let's get more good food next time.

257
00:13:50,370 --> 00:13:52,039
Your mother is so charismatic.

258
00:13:52,122 --> 00:13:53,123
When we're out...

259
00:13:53,206 --> 00:13:55,500
We're heading to the hotel now. See you!

260
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:57,336
Oh, I'm late!

261
00:14:11,433 --> 00:14:12,434
Tae-seop.

262
00:14:17,939 --> 00:14:18,982
Tae-seop.

263
00:14:28,825 --> 00:14:29,826
Ui-yeong!

264
00:14:37,084 --> 00:14:38,710
I thought she said she'd text me.

265
00:14:39,127 --> 00:14:41,004
Did her other date go well?

266
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:46,218
DIRECTOR AT HOUSE OF ANIMALS

267
00:14:50,639 --> 00:14:51,681
Yes, Director?

268
00:14:52,933 --> 00:14:55,769
I can't believe you're getting married.
Congratulations.

269
00:14:55,852 --> 00:14:57,062
Thank you.

270
00:14:57,270 --> 00:14:59,064
It's great that you work at a hotel.

271
00:14:59,147 --> 00:15:00,148
It's nothing.

272
00:15:00,232 --> 00:15:03,485
By the way, all consultations were full
on the weekend.

273
00:15:03,568 --> 00:15:05,320
They made a special slot for you

274
00:15:05,529 --> 00:15:07,864
so don't tell anyone else, okay?

275
00:15:08,573 --> 00:15:09,866
Don't worry.

276
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:13,120
Who can even afford to get married
at such a nice hotel?

277
00:15:14,704 --> 00:15:17,874
You two are so different.

278
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:19,376
That's why we get along.

279
00:15:19,584 --> 00:15:21,962
We did a group project in college

280
00:15:22,087 --> 00:15:25,549
and she prepared everything
for the presentation and the assignment

281
00:15:25,632 --> 00:15:27,426
in exchange for 100,000 won from me.

282
00:15:27,926 --> 00:15:29,803
- And we got...
- A-plus.

283
00:15:30,637 --> 00:15:33,723
Nobody valued me like you did.

284
00:15:34,558 --> 00:15:37,477
How can you still be single
when you're so smart?

285
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:39,354
- Honey.
- Yeah?

286
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:42,482
Don't you know anyone
you can set her up with?

287
00:15:42,774 --> 00:15:44,484
- Hmm?
- Did you think of any?

288
00:15:44,568 --> 00:15:46,361
I told you to think of some!

289
00:15:46,445 --> 00:15:48,196
Hey, you're making him uncomfortable.

290
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:49,906
It's fine.

291
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:51,450
Come on. Find someone.

292
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:52,784
Ms. Lee?

293
00:15:52,868 --> 00:15:54,077
Mr. Eun!

294
00:15:54,828 --> 00:15:57,289
I'm Eun Jeong-seok,
the General Manager at The Hills.

295
00:15:57,539 --> 00:16:00,917
I'll take you to the banquet room,
where the Wedding Manager is.

296
00:16:01,001 --> 00:16:02,252
You can leave it to me now.

297
00:16:02,335 --> 00:16:03,336
Please treat her well.

298
00:16:03,420 --> 00:16:04,880
We'll provide the best service.

299
00:16:07,507 --> 00:16:08,508
Text me later.

300
00:16:11,178 --> 00:16:12,179
Ui-yeong!

301
00:16:13,680 --> 00:16:14,806
What are you doing here?

302
00:16:17,809 --> 00:16:21,104
So, you were checking out of here

303
00:16:21,354 --> 00:16:23,315
and ran into Mr. Eun?

304
00:16:23,690 --> 00:16:25,734
What if people talk about you?

305
00:16:25,817 --> 00:16:28,153
What can I do?
I have to use my employee discount.

306
00:16:28,820 --> 00:16:32,115
And why should people be talking
about grown-ups having sex?

307
00:16:32,199 --> 00:16:33,742
Do you not do it?

308
00:16:34,451 --> 00:16:35,619
You're something else.

309
00:16:37,996 --> 00:16:42,000
But you know,
dating is starting to get boring.

310
00:16:42,876 --> 00:16:44,419
There's always a pattern.

311
00:16:44,628 --> 00:16:47,464
We meet, introduce ourselves,
eat a meal, and have sex.

312
00:16:47,547 --> 00:16:49,007
I can't meet a guy twice.

313
00:16:49,090 --> 00:16:50,759
Should I just become a celebrity fan?

314
00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:53,094
Why does that sound relatable?

315
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:00,852
I said you passed as my girlfriend
because I like you.

316
00:17:00,936 --> 00:17:02,312
I SAID YOU PASSED AS MY GIRLFRIEND
BECAUSE I LIKE YOU

317
00:17:03,563 --> 00:17:06,107
And I told you that you could use me
because I like you.

318
00:17:06,733 --> 00:17:11,071
Maybe I'll catch feelings for someone
if I go on a few more dates.

319
00:17:11,363 --> 00:17:13,823
They're all nice guys.

320
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:16,284
You'll give them that many chances?

321
00:17:16,409 --> 00:17:18,870
If they're that nice,
don't waste their time.

322
00:17:18,954 --> 00:17:20,997
Let them go so that they can find the one.

323
00:17:21,248 --> 00:17:23,833
If you're not interested in someone,
turn them down properly.

324
00:17:23,917 --> 00:17:26,127
That's also a part of being respectful
in dating.

325
00:17:33,593 --> 00:17:34,886
I'm sorry.

326
00:17:34,970 --> 00:17:37,138
I don't think we'd be a good match.

327
00:17:37,264 --> 00:17:39,015
I hope you find someone great.

328
00:17:42,352 --> 00:17:43,728
YOU WANT TO WATCH A MOVIE TONIGHT?

329
00:17:45,146 --> 00:17:47,274
Your mother is so charismatic.

330
00:17:47,357 --> 00:17:50,485
I can be your umbrella when you're out.

331
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:52,237
But you don't need one. It's too sunny.

332
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:54,030
I guess this is it for us.

333
00:17:54,114 --> 00:17:56,783
The end

334
00:17:56,866 --> 00:17:59,953
Know that they can reject you
just as much as you can reject them.

335
00:18:00,203 --> 00:18:02,122
That's how blind dates work.

336
00:18:02,622 --> 00:18:03,665
Yeah.

337
00:18:06,126 --> 00:18:07,127
Right.

338
00:18:22,350 --> 00:18:24,269
- Hello.
- Hello.

339
00:18:24,936 --> 00:18:26,354
How are you?

340
00:18:26,688 --> 00:18:28,273
Don't fight.

341
00:18:29,065 --> 00:18:30,984
Seoltang!

342
00:18:31,234 --> 00:18:32,235
Hello.

343
00:18:32,986 --> 00:18:35,322
Thanks for coming on such short notice.

344
00:18:35,864 --> 00:18:39,951
Seoltang, you're sparkling clean!
You look wonderful.

345
00:18:40,243 --> 00:18:43,955
Ask your new owner
for all the pets in the world, okay?

346
00:18:46,249 --> 00:18:47,709
Okay, thank you.

347
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:54,299
80, GEUMYEONGHWA 22-GIL,
PAJU, GYEONGGI-DO

348
00:18:55,091 --> 00:18:56,593
I don't want to adopt him anymore.

349
00:18:56,885 --> 00:18:57,886
Why?

350
00:18:58,303 --> 00:19:00,805
I'm sure
that wasn't an overnight decision.

351
00:19:00,889 --> 00:19:02,223
I liked him in the photos

352
00:19:02,307 --> 00:19:05,310
because he reminded me
of the dog I had as a kid.

353
00:19:05,393 --> 00:19:07,520
But he's too different in person.

354
00:19:07,604 --> 00:19:09,522
He's too big and too hairy.

355
00:19:09,689 --> 00:19:12,192
Maybe it's because he's a stray.
What if he has diseases?

356
00:19:12,275 --> 00:19:13,902
Please watch your mouth.

357
00:19:13,985 --> 00:19:16,738
It's not like animals understand humans.

358
00:19:17,155 --> 00:19:19,824
Animals can feel everything, too.

359
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:23,286
They can tell how we feel
based on our faces and voices.

360
00:19:23,370 --> 00:19:25,455
They know it when you don't like them.

361
00:19:25,747 --> 00:19:30,293
I hope you'll experience
what Seoltang just experienced one day.

362
00:19:30,377 --> 00:19:33,046
I don't think you'll get it
until you experience it yourself.

363
00:19:33,129 --> 00:19:34,172
Excuse me?

364
00:19:34,339 --> 00:19:35,340
Let's go, Seoltang.

365
00:19:35,632 --> 00:19:36,841
Excuse me? Let go.

366
00:19:36,925 --> 00:19:38,426
- Let's go.
- Excuse me?

367
00:19:38,510 --> 00:19:39,511
Say that again.

368
00:19:47,102 --> 00:19:48,103
POLICE WITHOUT CORRUPTION

369
00:19:48,186 --> 00:19:49,562
Oh, gosh, where?

370
00:19:50,230 --> 00:19:51,272
This way?

371
00:19:51,356 --> 00:19:53,066
Oh, goodness.

372
00:19:54,901 --> 00:19:56,736
- No running.
- Yes, sir.

373
00:19:58,571 --> 00:20:00,407
He tried to scam us!

374
00:20:00,490 --> 00:20:01,533
Hey!

375
00:20:02,534 --> 00:20:04,953
Mr. Song! Are you okay?

376
00:20:05,286 --> 00:20:06,746
Who the hell do you think you are?

377
00:20:07,038 --> 00:20:10,625
You think dogs are toys?
Come on, you should know better!

378
00:20:10,792 --> 00:20:13,378
You need to think it through
before adopting a pet!

379
00:20:13,461 --> 00:20:14,754
And be responsible!

380
00:20:14,838 --> 00:20:16,339
What the hell are you saying?

381
00:20:16,423 --> 00:20:17,549
What did you say?

382
00:20:17,632 --> 00:20:20,260
Gosh, even dogs are better than you are.

383
00:20:20,343 --> 00:20:21,344
Come here.

384
00:20:21,428 --> 00:20:24,180
- Are you okay, my Seoltang?
- Who the hell are you?

385
00:20:24,973 --> 00:20:26,558
What do you think you're doing?

386
00:20:26,641 --> 00:20:28,143
- Are you okay?
- Hey!

387
00:20:28,226 --> 00:20:30,854
- Did you just push me?
- So what?

388
00:20:31,271 --> 00:20:33,314
Stop pissing me off.

389
00:20:34,441 --> 00:20:35,942
- Say it again. What?
- Please.

390
00:20:36,025 --> 00:20:37,736
- Stop.
- What was it?

391
00:20:37,819 --> 00:20:39,529
- Stop it!
- Sir!

392
00:20:39,612 --> 00:20:41,990
- What the hell are you doing?
- Hey!

393
00:20:49,205 --> 00:20:53,001
PAJU SEOBU POLICE STATION

394
00:20:53,752 --> 00:20:56,337
I didn't think you'd call me
to the police station.

395
00:20:56,421 --> 00:21:00,008
I thought you'd handle it
more like a grown-up.

396
00:21:06,389 --> 00:21:09,017
We had good teamwork, though.

397
00:21:09,184 --> 00:21:12,937
I thought you were gentle.
You're quite a fighter.

398
00:21:13,021 --> 00:21:14,397
You know how to hold a grudge.

399
00:21:14,481 --> 00:21:18,359
I lost it when he gave up Seoltang
five minutes after meeting him.

400
00:21:18,443 --> 00:21:20,361
That's terrible.

401
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:24,866
Can people stop setting such record?
It's nothing to be proud of.

402
00:21:24,949 --> 00:21:25,992
I know.

403
00:21:26,367 --> 00:21:28,036
Oh, no, that's not good.

404
00:21:28,286 --> 00:21:29,788
You're allergic to dogs.

405
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:33,416
I can keep him
and return him to the shelter on Monday.

406
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:36,085
No, I'll take him.
I'll be fine with my meds for a few days.

407
00:21:36,169 --> 00:21:37,545
If that's what you want.

408
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:39,005
Seoltang

409
00:21:39,631 --> 00:21:42,342
I guess
an even better home is waiting for you.

410
00:21:46,679 --> 00:21:48,807
It's mine.

411
00:21:48,890 --> 00:21:49,891
Oh.

412
00:21:53,978 --> 00:21:56,356
Mr. Eun, I heard my friend booked
the wedding hall.

413
00:21:56,439 --> 00:21:57,857
Thanks for coming on your day off

414
00:21:57,941 --> 00:22:00,068
I'm touched once again.

415
00:22:00,151 --> 00:22:02,111
Sure. Smiley face.

416
00:22:03,488 --> 00:22:05,198
Are you waiting for someone to text you?

417
00:22:05,281 --> 00:22:07,075
Yeah, Ui-yeong.

418
00:22:11,079 --> 00:22:12,372
Oh.

419
00:22:14,082 --> 00:22:16,876
I was the matchmaker

420
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:19,087
so I should be honest and tell you.

421
00:22:19,587 --> 00:22:21,005
Ui-yeong...

422
00:22:21,089 --> 00:22:23,550
I know she went on another blind date.
I saw her.

423
00:22:25,552 --> 00:22:26,886
You saw her?

424
00:22:27,178 --> 00:22:28,471
And you're still waiting?

425
00:22:29,556 --> 00:22:33,810
She said she'd text me,
and it's not exactly over yet.

426
00:22:34,394 --> 00:22:38,022
I can't tell if you're confident
or just stupid.

427
00:22:39,732 --> 00:22:42,861
I'll know for sure
if I just see her one more time.

428
00:22:46,865 --> 00:22:49,993
Man, that's tricky.

429
00:22:50,285 --> 00:22:53,788
I'm a matchmaker, not Cupid.

430
00:22:57,458 --> 00:23:01,337
Run into her one more time, then.

431
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:04,465
Sorry? What do you mean?

432
00:23:04,549 --> 00:23:07,343
I'll fix it for you.

433
00:23:07,594 --> 00:23:09,596
It's a small world at the hotel.

434
00:23:09,679 --> 00:23:11,389
It's a workplace to some

435
00:23:11,472 --> 00:23:14,434
where they have to stay all day every day.

436
00:23:14,809 --> 00:23:17,353
And to others,
it's a place for business meetings

437
00:23:17,604 --> 00:23:20,565
or a nice place to have coffee
with their friends.

438
00:23:21,107 --> 00:23:23,610
So, just run into her at the hotel.

439
00:23:25,028 --> 00:23:26,571
Oh.

440
00:23:30,199 --> 00:23:31,534
"Hey, Ui-yeong!"

441
00:23:32,035 --> 00:23:33,912
"Is this the hotel you work at?"

442
00:23:34,871 --> 00:23:37,540
"Wow, I see."

443
00:23:37,957 --> 00:23:40,710
"I'm here to meet a friend."

444
00:23:44,047 --> 00:23:46,758
"What a coincidence."

445
00:23:46,841 --> 00:23:48,843
"Would you like to grab lunch together?"

446
00:23:50,219 --> 00:23:52,180
Why would I shake her hand?

447
00:23:54,307 --> 00:23:55,433
Ui-yeong...

448
00:23:56,684 --> 00:23:58,895
"Ui-yeong."

449
00:24:00,563 --> 00:24:02,148
Seoltang...

450
00:24:03,149 --> 00:24:04,359
What do I do?

451
00:24:06,027 --> 00:24:07,195
It's called "HOME."

452
00:24:07,278 --> 00:24:11,240
It's quite popular among people
interested in home renovations.

453
00:24:11,324 --> 00:24:12,784
COMPANY PORTFOLIO FOR HOME

454
00:24:13,493 --> 00:24:16,663
They also do renovations for cafés.

455
00:24:16,788 --> 00:24:18,665
We're not dilly-dallying.

456
00:24:18,748 --> 00:24:21,334
Let's just stick with Homage.
We work with them all the time.

457
00:24:22,001 --> 00:24:24,712
I know Homage is great,
but so is this place.

458
00:24:24,837 --> 00:24:28,549
Why don't we choose between the two
after they submit their proposals?

459
00:24:28,925 --> 00:24:32,387
That's extra work for us.
Is that necessary?

460
00:24:32,470 --> 00:24:35,223
An important part of our jobs is
to create a great space.

461
00:24:35,306 --> 00:24:36,641
Let's ask for a proposal.

462
00:24:36,724 --> 00:24:38,184
Why don't we give them two weeks?

463
00:24:38,309 --> 00:24:40,561
Just give them a week
and say it can be a rough draft.

464
00:24:40,645 --> 00:24:44,148
A week sounds too short.

465
00:24:44,232 --> 00:24:46,442
Let's do ten days, then.

466
00:24:46,526 --> 00:24:50,113
Why even ask me
if you'll just do whatever you want?

467
00:24:50,405 --> 00:24:53,783
I'll call Homage.
You can take care of the rest, then.

468
00:24:53,866 --> 00:24:55,910
Okay, I'll contact HOME.

469
00:24:55,994 --> 00:24:57,161
No, Sae-byeok will.

470
00:24:57,286 --> 00:25:00,665
Why don't we ask her to contact them
since she found them?

471
00:25:00,748 --> 00:25:02,375
I'll send the e-mail.

472
00:25:02,458 --> 00:25:04,210
Let's leave her to set the details.

473
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:07,213
Are you up for it?

474
00:25:07,672 --> 00:25:09,799
Yes, I'll do it.

475
00:25:11,259 --> 00:25:13,803
PROPOSAL FOR THE HILLS SEOUL'S COLLAB
WITH DEERFIDDICH

476
00:25:13,886 --> 00:25:14,887
YOUR MAIL HAS BEEN SENT

477
00:25:14,971 --> 00:25:15,972
All done.

478
00:25:16,055 --> 00:25:17,098
- Sae-byeok.
- Yes?

479
00:25:17,181 --> 00:25:20,018
I e-mailed them.
You can call them and go home.

480
00:25:20,226 --> 00:25:21,310
Okay.

481
00:25:21,394 --> 00:25:23,104
- Good work today.
- See you tomorrow.

482
00:25:23,187 --> 00:25:24,731
- Go home soon, okay?
- Okay!

483
00:25:38,870 --> 00:25:40,580
Hello, this is Lee Eun-ho from HOME.

484
00:25:40,872 --> 00:25:42,081
Hello.

485
00:25:42,165 --> 00:25:44,959
I'm Sim Sae-byeok from Purchasing
at The Hills Seoul.

486
00:25:45,043 --> 00:25:47,545
We just sent you an e-mail.

487
00:25:49,672 --> 00:25:50,840
Oh.

488
00:25:51,632 --> 00:25:53,676
- It's a pop-up store?
- That's right.

489
00:25:54,177 --> 00:25:56,512
HOME WILL CHECK THE E-MAIL AND LET US KNOW

490
00:26:04,896 --> 00:26:06,439
She's the intern.

491
00:26:06,522 --> 00:26:08,316
- Who?
- You know, with Do-hyun.

492
00:26:08,649 --> 00:26:10,443
- That's the intern?
- Yeah!

493
00:26:12,403 --> 00:26:14,614
Is work just a playground for people
these days?

494
00:26:14,697 --> 00:26:15,823
Tell me about it.

495
00:26:27,376 --> 00:26:31,005
Mr. Kang, can I talk to you for a sec?

496
00:26:36,803 --> 00:26:38,638
No, I'll bring it.

497
00:26:41,891 --> 00:26:43,893
Thank you. Enjoy your drink.

498
00:26:43,976 --> 00:26:44,977
Thank you.

499
00:26:56,572 --> 00:26:58,866
Did you think about it?

500
00:26:59,617 --> 00:27:00,618
Yes.

501
00:27:02,537 --> 00:27:05,915
I don't want to make things awkward
with Ui-yeong

502
00:27:06,582 --> 00:27:09,627
and I need to focus
on finding a job right now.

503
00:27:10,753 --> 00:27:12,004
I'm sorry.

504
00:27:16,092 --> 00:27:18,719
I've been rejected for a similar reason.

505
00:27:19,220 --> 00:27:21,514
I backed down then because I was a nobody

506
00:27:22,682 --> 00:27:24,100
but things are different now.

507
00:27:24,308 --> 00:27:26,102
I can pay for all our meals

508
00:27:26,185 --> 00:27:28,646
and support you until you land a job.

509
00:27:28,813 --> 00:27:30,690
Think about what works best for you.

510
00:27:30,773 --> 00:27:33,651
To be honest, you just made it harder
for me to get a job.

511
00:27:33,734 --> 00:27:35,903
I haven't even proved myself yet

512
00:27:35,987 --> 00:27:39,824
and people at the hotel already know me
because of you.

513
00:27:40,616 --> 00:27:43,911
I want to do really well on this project.

514
00:27:44,662 --> 00:27:47,081
Please let me focus on work.

515
00:27:49,208 --> 00:27:52,086
Please excuse me, then.

516
00:28:16,652 --> 00:28:18,613
Do we need more frame structure
for the legs?

517
00:28:19,363 --> 00:28:21,949
We're going to use ropes
and minimize using frames.

518
00:28:23,242 --> 00:28:25,244
Eun-ho, did you see the e-mail?

519
00:28:25,703 --> 00:28:27,330
- Which one?
- The pop-up at The Hills.

520
00:28:27,413 --> 00:28:29,665
Yeah, but I'm going to turn it down.

521
00:28:29,749 --> 00:28:31,250
We're too busy already.

522
00:28:31,334 --> 00:28:33,711
You don't even like
these temporary projects.

523
00:28:33,794 --> 00:28:35,338
That's true.

524
00:28:36,839 --> 00:28:38,299
But we need to take this.

525
00:28:39,425 --> 00:28:42,136
What are you talking about?
We have enough work already.

526
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:44,472
No, I want to do this.

527
00:28:44,555 --> 00:28:46,599
Huh? Where are you going?

528
00:28:46,933 --> 00:28:48,517
To check out the space at the hotel.

529
00:28:48,684 --> 00:28:50,728
Right now? Huh?

530
00:28:51,103 --> 00:28:52,897
- Are you really doing it?
- Yeah.

531
00:28:53,189 --> 00:28:55,316
I was going to go, anyway.

532
00:28:57,151 --> 00:28:58,945
- Ui-yeong.
- Yeah?

533
00:28:59,612 --> 00:29:02,698
I got a reply from Mr. Lee at HOME.

534
00:29:02,782 --> 00:29:04,325
He wants to participate in the bid.

535
00:29:04,408 --> 00:29:06,285
Really? That's great!

536
00:29:06,494 --> 00:29:10,081
Sorry about leaving you and Hyun-min
to do all the work.

537
00:29:10,164 --> 00:29:12,458
I'll buy you a nice meal soon.

538
00:29:27,348 --> 00:29:28,766
So, this is it.

539
00:29:30,059 --> 00:29:31,060
Oh?

540
00:29:34,689 --> 00:29:36,315
- I'm so sorry.
- Are you okay?

541
00:29:36,899 --> 00:29:37,900
I'm okay, thank you.

542
00:29:49,495 --> 00:29:51,038
I'm sure I'll see her again.

543
00:29:56,002 --> 00:29:58,004
- I'll go after I take this call.
- Okay.

544
00:30:01,382 --> 00:30:02,383
Hello?

545
00:30:02,466 --> 00:30:03,884
Is this Ms. Lee Ui-yeong?

546
00:30:04,051 --> 00:30:06,846
I'm Kim Su-on. Eun-mi gave me your number.

547
00:30:07,013 --> 00:30:09,932
Oh, I see. Hello.

548
00:30:10,349 --> 00:30:12,268
Sorry about calling you out of the blue.

549
00:30:12,435 --> 00:30:14,603
Are you free tomorrow evening?

550
00:30:19,567 --> 00:30:21,235
Eun-mi's told me so much about you.

551
00:30:21,319 --> 00:30:23,112
She said you were such a nice person

552
00:30:23,195 --> 00:30:25,281
so I wasn't expecting
such a beautiful woman.

553
00:30:26,991 --> 00:30:28,326
But you're beautiful.

554
00:30:28,951 --> 00:30:32,163
KIM SU-ON, 35, RUNS A FAMILY BUSINESS

555
00:30:32,246 --> 00:30:33,873
Oh, thank you.

556
00:30:35,207 --> 00:30:39,045
I heard you were friends with Ho-jin
for a long time.

557
00:30:39,128 --> 00:30:40,129
Oh, that bastard...

558
00:30:41,047 --> 00:30:43,090
I've been friends with him for 20 years.

559
00:30:43,799 --> 00:30:47,053
We should go on a double date one day.

560
00:30:53,517 --> 00:30:55,811
So, what do your parents like to do?

561
00:30:56,520 --> 00:30:58,856
My parents? Not me?

562
00:30:58,939 --> 00:30:59,940
Yeah.

563
00:31:00,524 --> 00:31:01,650
Oh...

564
00:31:01,817 --> 00:31:05,321
My mom's been doing yoga
for a very long time.

565
00:31:05,780 --> 00:31:09,825
My dad used to love fishing and camping
back in the day

566
00:31:10,242 --> 00:31:11,577
but not anymore.

567
00:31:11,660 --> 00:31:14,205
I heard your father works
for the railroad.

568
00:31:16,082 --> 00:31:17,750
Yeah, he does.

569
00:31:17,833 --> 00:31:19,960
And you don't live with him
because of his work.

570
00:31:22,421 --> 00:31:24,715
It's not just because of his work.

571
00:31:25,383 --> 00:31:28,344
I don't know the whole story
because it's between my parents

572
00:31:28,761 --> 00:31:32,640
but their personalities and values were
too different.

573
00:31:32,848 --> 00:31:35,017
They've been living separately
since I was a kid.

574
00:31:35,309 --> 00:31:36,310
I see.

575
00:31:36,811 --> 00:31:38,687
So, are they divorced?

576
00:31:39,271 --> 00:31:41,482
No, they just live separately.

577
00:31:41,565 --> 00:31:42,608
I see.

578
00:31:43,651 --> 00:31:45,778
I'm so glad.

579
00:31:46,237 --> 00:31:47,238
"Glad"?

580
00:31:47,321 --> 00:31:49,407
You seem like you were raised
in a loving family.

581
00:31:49,824 --> 00:31:52,535
I wouldn't have known that wasn't the case
if you didn't tell me.

582
00:32:22,356 --> 00:32:23,607
Hey, Eun-mi.

583
00:32:23,899 --> 00:32:25,526
I heard you had dinner with Su-on.

584
00:32:25,609 --> 00:32:27,486
How did it go? Isn't he so funny?

585
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:31,907
He did say a lot of not-so-funny things
with confidence.

586
00:32:31,991 --> 00:32:33,742
He's just honest.

587
00:32:34,076 --> 00:32:35,327
He told me

588
00:32:35,411 --> 00:32:38,289
he's only interested in flawless women

589
00:32:38,372 --> 00:32:39,832
but wants to see you again.

590
00:32:43,502 --> 00:32:44,795
What does he mean by that?

591
00:32:45,045 --> 00:32:47,756
Oh, I didn't know
your parents didn't live together.

592
00:32:48,090 --> 00:32:50,301
Why didn't you tell me?
I thought we were friends.

593
00:32:50,551 --> 00:32:52,052
I never tried to hide it from you.

594
00:32:52,386 --> 00:32:54,555
It's not like I have to tell that
to all my friends.

595
00:32:54,722 --> 00:32:58,392
The point is, things worked out,
and he wants to see you again.

596
00:32:58,476 --> 00:33:02,188
Oh, he wants to know
if your parents have a retirement fund.

597
00:33:02,980 --> 00:33:04,023
What?

598
00:33:04,857 --> 00:33:06,150
Why does he need to know that?

599
00:33:06,484 --> 00:33:08,360
It's good for you to ask him, too.

600
00:33:08,444 --> 00:33:11,572
It doesn't have to be in detail.
Just ask him if they're financially okay.

601
00:33:13,324 --> 00:33:15,159
What a ridiculous question.

602
00:33:15,576 --> 00:33:16,577
Bye.

603
00:34:28,148 --> 00:34:29,567
DAD

604
00:34:33,988 --> 00:34:37,199
I can't call him out of nowhere
just to ask him that.

605
00:34:43,581 --> 00:34:44,623
Hey, Mom.

606
00:34:45,958 --> 00:34:47,876
- What are you doing?
- Nothing much.

607
00:34:50,588 --> 00:34:52,339
Don't be on your phone all night.

608
00:34:52,423 --> 00:34:54,425
I'm not in high school anymore.

609
00:34:54,508 --> 00:34:55,509
Whatever.

610
00:35:03,976 --> 00:35:05,811
Yeah, that's pushing it.

611
00:35:06,353 --> 00:35:07,688
My parents' retirement?

612
00:35:07,771 --> 00:35:10,149
Guys didn't need to know that to date me
in the past.

613
00:35:14,903 --> 00:35:17,948
I don't think Su-on and I are compatible.

614
00:35:18,449 --> 00:35:20,034
Please tell him that.

615
00:35:26,498 --> 00:35:27,583
Alright.

616
00:35:28,542 --> 00:35:30,502
Huh? What?

617
00:35:33,005 --> 00:35:34,340
I forgot to take the tag off!

618
00:35:34,798 --> 00:35:36,508
Time for me to return it.

619
00:35:39,762 --> 00:35:41,805
This is a lot. What do we do?

620
00:35:42,056 --> 00:35:43,182
It's all due this week.

621
00:35:43,265 --> 00:35:44,600
- What?
- This week.

622
00:36:13,212 --> 00:36:15,547
You know how we're getting proposals
from the companies?

623
00:36:15,631 --> 00:36:17,591
Let's just get one from Homage.

624
00:36:17,675 --> 00:36:19,176
Sorry? Why?

625
00:36:19,259 --> 00:36:21,720
Why bother with the others?
That's a waste of time.

626
00:36:21,887 --> 00:36:24,056
We could've just gone with Homage
from the start.

627
00:36:24,139 --> 00:36:27,101
We're just asking one more company
so you have more work.

628
00:36:27,184 --> 00:36:28,936
Let's keep things simple.

629
00:36:29,186 --> 00:36:32,815
I'll ask Ui-yeong about it.

630
00:36:32,898 --> 00:36:36,860
Are you saying you need her permission
for what I just said?

631
00:36:38,070 --> 00:36:40,030
No, that's not what I mean.

632
00:36:40,906 --> 00:36:42,074
I'm sorry.

633
00:36:44,618 --> 00:36:45,911
- Sae-byeok.
- Yes?

634
00:36:45,994 --> 00:36:48,789
It takes competence
to handle a situation like this.

635
00:36:49,039 --> 00:36:53,168
I'll make sure Homage prepares
the perfect proposal.

636
00:36:53,252 --> 00:36:55,963
Your job is to tell HOME
that we don't need their proposal.

637
00:36:56,046 --> 00:36:57,214
Okay, noted.

638
00:37:08,308 --> 00:37:09,685
- Hello.
- Hello.

639
00:37:09,768 --> 00:37:11,603
CONFERENCE ROOM

640
00:37:11,687 --> 00:37:13,188
I'm Oh Man-joong, the CEO of Homage.

641
00:37:13,272 --> 00:37:15,858
I love your business card.

642
00:37:20,362 --> 00:37:23,782
I set up a successful exhibition
at The Place Hotel this year

643
00:37:23,866 --> 00:37:25,951
and what was the project
that ended last week?

644
00:37:26,660 --> 00:37:28,829
Oh, the Bella Art Gallery.

645
00:37:29,371 --> 00:37:33,625
As mentioned in the e-mail,
our exhibition is focused on the objet.

646
00:37:33,709 --> 00:37:35,335
We'll make some display cases, then.

647
00:37:35,544 --> 00:37:39,047
Show them the jewelry shop we opened
at the New World Department Store in 2017.

648
00:37:39,131 --> 00:37:40,716
- Show them the design.
- Yes, sir.

649
00:37:48,974 --> 00:37:50,559
Oh, this shop.

650
00:37:53,645 --> 00:37:55,314
We have to talk about the deadline.

651
00:37:55,397 --> 00:37:56,982
We'd like the store to be ready...

652
00:37:57,065 --> 00:37:59,443
We're not running a corner shop here.

653
00:37:59,526 --> 00:38:01,612
We've done hundreds of pop-ups.

654
00:38:01,737 --> 00:38:05,073
We work with city halls, malls,
and art galleries.

655
00:38:05,157 --> 00:38:06,784
You think we'd miss a deadline?

656
00:38:07,034 --> 00:38:09,661
I'm sure you wouldn't,
but we still need to confirm it...

657
00:38:09,745 --> 00:38:11,747
Sara, show them the proposal.

658
00:38:11,830 --> 00:38:12,831
Yes, sir.

659
00:38:16,543 --> 00:38:18,796
You have it already?

660
00:38:22,007 --> 00:38:23,133
My gosh.

661
00:38:27,346 --> 00:38:31,016
That's a lot of detail
in such a short period.

662
00:38:31,099 --> 00:38:33,268
We'll use Lauan plywood

663
00:38:33,560 --> 00:38:36,021
to highlight the vintage vibe
of the whiskey.

664
00:38:36,104 --> 00:38:38,690
We'll finish some parts with Formica

665
00:38:38,774 --> 00:38:41,527
to add Deerfiddich's signature color
to the wood.

666
00:38:42,361 --> 00:38:44,238
You got it done so well in no time!

667
00:38:44,905 --> 00:38:46,657
You're a pro, indeed.

668
00:38:47,741 --> 00:38:48,992
What do you think?

669
00:38:49,076 --> 00:38:51,787
What? Oh, it's great.

670
00:38:58,377 --> 00:39:00,629
It looks very classy.

671
00:39:01,171 --> 00:39:02,798
- Great work.
- Good job.

672
00:39:02,881 --> 00:39:04,591
- See you.
- This way.

673
00:39:05,092 --> 00:39:07,553
Thanks so much, sir.

674
00:39:07,636 --> 00:39:09,721
- Bye.
- I love your outfit today, too.

675
00:39:09,805 --> 00:39:12,391
Do you have time after this?

676
00:39:12,808 --> 00:39:15,143
How about a drink together?

677
00:39:19,106 --> 00:39:20,482
Oh, Sae-byeok

678
00:39:20,566 --> 00:39:23,819
have you not scheduled a meeting
with HOME's CEO yet?

679
00:39:25,654 --> 00:39:27,656
Oh, well, that's...

680
00:39:28,073 --> 00:39:30,284
The CEO called

681
00:39:32,119 --> 00:39:33,620
and he...

682
00:39:34,413 --> 00:39:36,164
Something's going on at HOME

683
00:39:36,707 --> 00:39:38,750
so he doesn't have time.

684
00:39:40,127 --> 00:39:41,753
He said he needed to drop our project.

685
00:39:41,837 --> 00:39:42,838
Drop it?

686
00:39:43,130 --> 00:39:46,049
Didn't he agree on the project
a while ago?

687
00:39:51,179 --> 00:39:53,515
That's why you seem so down.

688
00:39:53,765 --> 00:39:56,184
You must be so disappointed.
You worked so hard for it.

689
00:39:56,393 --> 00:39:58,687
It's okay. This happens from time to time.

690
00:39:59,229 --> 00:40:00,272
Okay.

691
00:40:00,606 --> 00:40:04,192
I'm glad we found talented people
to work with.

692
00:40:04,276 --> 00:40:06,028
That's a huge relief.

693
00:40:07,195 --> 00:40:08,280
It's okay, Sae-byeok.

694
00:40:08,614 --> 00:40:09,948
- Okay.
- Yeah.

695
00:40:14,828 --> 00:40:16,496
- Let's clean up.
- Okay.

696
00:40:27,716 --> 00:40:29,885
Is this layout too complicated?

697
00:40:30,844 --> 00:40:33,055
That looks nice!

698
00:40:34,056 --> 00:40:35,265
It's perfect

699
00:40:37,309 --> 00:40:38,435
but we're out.

700
00:40:39,645 --> 00:40:40,687
What?

701
00:40:41,772 --> 00:40:44,107
What do you mean?
We haven't even had a meeting.

702
00:40:45,817 --> 00:40:47,361
You got a cigarette?

703
00:40:47,527 --> 00:40:48,695
I quit ages ago.

704
00:40:50,656 --> 00:40:53,659
I hate how they just said
it was an internal decision.

705
00:40:53,742 --> 00:40:56,703
They could've at least said
we were over their budget!

706
00:40:56,870 --> 00:40:58,872
This is just plain disrespectful!

707
00:40:58,956 --> 00:41:01,333
I bet they already decided on a company
before asking us.

708
00:41:01,625 --> 00:41:04,044
Do they think it's our first time
getting dropped?

709
00:41:04,544 --> 00:41:08,882
If that's really the case,
it's good that it ended here.

710
00:41:10,092 --> 00:41:12,928
Didn't you pull multiple all-nighters
for the project?

711
00:41:13,512 --> 00:41:15,639
You want to get some fresh air somewhere?

712
00:41:16,264 --> 00:41:18,767
Sure, let's take Sua.

713
00:41:26,358 --> 00:41:28,151
- See you tomorrow.
- See you.

714
00:41:29,945 --> 00:41:30,988
Hello?

715
00:41:31,279 --> 00:41:33,615
I guess you didn't save my number.

716
00:41:33,699 --> 00:41:35,117
I'm Su-on.

717
00:41:35,784 --> 00:41:38,537
I told Eun-mi I wanted to see you again.

718
00:41:38,954 --> 00:41:41,498
Did Eun-mi not tell him what I said?

719
00:41:41,707 --> 00:41:43,000
Do you have time after work?

720
00:41:43,333 --> 00:41:46,294
I'm near your hotel right now
for something else.

721
00:41:46,753 --> 00:41:48,088
Oh, are you?

722
00:41:49,548 --> 00:41:51,425
Sure, I have time.

723
00:41:53,552 --> 00:41:54,594
Okay.

724
00:42:05,856 --> 00:42:07,566
I brought it to return it, though.

725
00:42:17,200 --> 00:42:20,454
You look great in that dress, too.

726
00:42:21,788 --> 00:42:23,623
It's hard to look so good in pink.

727
00:42:25,292 --> 00:42:26,501
Thank you.

728
00:42:27,627 --> 00:42:29,296
Su-on

729
00:42:29,629 --> 00:42:33,050
I heard you had questions
about my parents' retirement plans.

730
00:42:33,842 --> 00:42:35,469
Yeah, why?

731
00:42:37,179 --> 00:42:41,683
It's not like we're seeing each other now
to get married.

732
00:42:41,975 --> 00:42:46,063
With that said, their retirement plans are
between me and my parents.

733
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:49,733
It's not for you to know about
or prepare for.

734
00:42:50,859 --> 00:42:51,943
Oh, right.

735
00:42:52,903 --> 00:42:54,029
I get what you mean.

736
00:42:54,654 --> 00:42:56,406
It's okay. Just forget what I said.

737
00:42:59,785 --> 00:43:02,746
Let's lighten the mood.
Should we order some wine?

738
00:43:03,246 --> 00:43:04,289
Sure.

739
00:43:05,457 --> 00:43:07,125
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

740
00:43:10,962 --> 00:43:13,381
We'll get a cheese platter

741
00:43:15,759 --> 00:43:16,843
with this wine.

742
00:43:17,636 --> 00:43:18,720
Jeong-u?

743
00:43:18,845 --> 00:43:20,180
I'll get that ready for you.

744
00:43:36,905 --> 00:43:38,323
SHIN JI-SU

745
00:43:38,949 --> 00:43:40,075
Oh, right.

746
00:43:40,158 --> 00:43:42,452
Jeong-u had a tattoo on his neck.

747
00:43:59,970 --> 00:44:01,847
I heard you could drink quite a bit.

748
00:44:01,930 --> 00:44:03,557
How much can you drink, exactly?

749
00:44:04,391 --> 00:44:07,686
It depends on the drink,
but I can handle a bottle of wine.

750
00:44:07,853 --> 00:44:09,563
That's a lot more than me.

751
00:44:09,980 --> 00:44:12,440
I should pour some more for you, then.

752
00:44:14,568 --> 00:44:17,821
Please excuse me.
I need to use the bathroom.

753
00:44:17,946 --> 00:44:18,947
Okay.

754
00:44:26,872 --> 00:44:28,206
Excuse me.

755
00:44:29,541 --> 00:44:33,295
Maybe this question is a bit random

756
00:44:33,503 --> 00:44:36,756
but do you have a twin brother?

757
00:44:37,465 --> 00:44:39,342
No, I don't.

758
00:44:39,759 --> 00:44:42,012
Oh, sorry about that.

759
00:44:44,139 --> 00:44:45,348
My last name is different

760
00:44:46,099 --> 00:44:47,976
from the guy you think is my twin, right?

761
00:44:48,727 --> 00:44:49,728
Sorry?

762
00:44:49,978 --> 00:44:52,647
My last name is Shin, and his is Lee.

763
00:44:54,191 --> 00:44:55,525
Oh, that's true...

764
00:44:58,612 --> 00:44:59,696
It's you, right?

765
00:45:00,530 --> 00:45:01,531
You're Jeong-u.

766
00:45:02,032 --> 00:45:03,116
What are you doing here?

767
00:45:03,241 --> 00:45:05,285
Can't you tell? I work here.

768
00:45:05,368 --> 00:45:06,494
Yeah, why here?

769
00:45:08,163 --> 00:45:09,289
Are you on another date?

770
00:45:10,415 --> 00:45:13,251
- You're really desperate.
- What?

771
00:45:13,335 --> 00:45:15,962
You also couldn't stop talking
about finding a guy then.

772
00:45:19,090 --> 00:45:20,842
He's not so bad.

773
00:45:20,926 --> 00:45:23,970
He has eyes, a nose, and lips.

774
00:45:24,054 --> 00:45:25,513
He's decently dressed.

775
00:45:25,931 --> 00:45:27,098
That's what you're into.

776
00:45:27,891 --> 00:45:29,267
What am I into?

777
00:45:29,351 --> 00:45:30,560
Good luck.

778
00:45:30,727 --> 00:45:33,271
If you don't like him

779
00:45:34,356 --> 00:45:36,066
do this.

780
00:45:36,566 --> 00:45:38,235
That's your sign, okay?

781
00:45:38,944 --> 00:45:39,986
Got it?

782
00:45:40,487 --> 00:45:41,529
Hey...

783
00:45:43,657 --> 00:45:44,783
Man!

784
00:45:46,326 --> 00:45:47,744
What was that about?

785
00:46:04,761 --> 00:46:07,013
Hey, Su-on

786
00:46:07,305 --> 00:46:10,308
why don't we go
somewhere more comfortable?

787
00:46:13,103 --> 00:46:15,647
Sure, do you know a place?

788
00:46:15,772 --> 00:46:17,732
Not really.

789
00:46:18,024 --> 00:46:20,443
But anywhere would be better than here.

790
00:46:20,860 --> 00:46:23,321
Oh, okay.

791
00:46:24,281 --> 00:46:27,158
Sure, then.
I'll just quickly use the bathroom.

792
00:46:27,325 --> 00:46:28,326
Okay.

793
00:46:41,298 --> 00:46:43,049
Seriously, what is he doing here?

794
00:46:43,300 --> 00:46:44,718
Hey, Eun-mi told me

795
00:46:45,176 --> 00:46:46,928
Ui-yeong didn't want a second date.

796
00:46:49,180 --> 00:46:51,808
How dare she reject me? She's a nobody.

797
00:46:52,392 --> 00:46:54,185
I got bored, so I asked her out again.

798
00:46:55,020 --> 00:46:56,521
But you know what's hilarious?

799
00:46:57,564 --> 00:46:59,524
She didn't even take
the tag off her dress.

800
00:47:00,692 --> 00:47:03,778
Do I get to keep her if I take it off?

801
00:47:06,197 --> 00:47:07,449
Seriously.

802
00:47:09,576 --> 00:47:10,577
Yeah.

803
00:47:11,828 --> 00:47:13,830
No idea.
She wants to go somewhere comfortable.

804
00:47:14,831 --> 00:47:16,875
Where should I take her? A motel?

805
00:47:19,294 --> 00:47:20,962
Oh, it's so slippery.

806
00:47:21,379 --> 00:47:23,256
Sorry about that.

807
00:47:27,177 --> 00:47:28,261
Hey...

808
00:47:30,263 --> 00:47:33,308
But the floor is dry.

809
00:47:37,479 --> 00:47:38,563
- Let's get out.
- Huh?

810
00:47:38,646 --> 00:47:40,273
- What?
- I'll tell you outside.

811
00:47:40,357 --> 00:47:41,983
- Let go.
- What's going on?

812
00:47:43,068 --> 00:47:45,153
Su-on, he's...

813
00:47:45,236 --> 00:47:46,321
Ui-yeong.

814
00:47:46,488 --> 00:47:48,281
I guess your taste in men has changed.

815
00:47:49,032 --> 00:47:52,285
You pushed me in the bathroom
on purpose, didn't you?

816
00:47:52,369 --> 00:47:53,620
Do you know him?

817
00:47:53,828 --> 00:47:55,872
No, I don't. Let's just leave.

818
00:47:55,955 --> 00:47:57,248
Are you really going to leave?

819
00:47:58,083 --> 00:48:00,293
I know how you really feel.

820
00:48:00,627 --> 00:48:02,670
You came here because you missed me.

821
00:48:03,129 --> 00:48:04,506
What the hell are you doing?

822
00:48:04,589 --> 00:48:07,175
I couldn't even sleep or eat
because I missed you.

823
00:48:07,258 --> 00:48:09,344
Look at me. Don't I look thinner?

824
00:48:09,803 --> 00:48:10,804
Hey!

825
00:48:10,887 --> 00:48:13,932
Oh, so, she used me.

826
00:48:14,224 --> 00:48:17,018
- What?
- What a damn shitty day.

827
00:48:17,560 --> 00:48:19,312
You acted all classy

828
00:48:19,396 --> 00:48:20,980
so I didn't know you were a whore.

829
00:48:21,147 --> 00:48:22,899
You know who the real whore is?

830
00:48:22,982 --> 00:48:25,193
- Did you just push me?
- Stop.

831
00:48:25,402 --> 00:48:26,653
- Stop.
- Damn it.

832
00:48:26,736 --> 00:48:28,196
- Stop it.
- Hey!

833
00:48:29,531 --> 00:48:30,657
Are you okay?

834
00:48:30,740 --> 00:48:32,283
- What's going on?
- Is he okay?

835
00:48:32,617 --> 00:48:33,618
Are you hurt?

836
00:48:33,701 --> 00:48:35,662
You pushed me first.

837
00:48:38,164 --> 00:48:39,332
You're kidding me.

838
00:48:41,167 --> 00:48:42,502
I'm sorry.

839
00:48:56,641 --> 00:48:57,725
I'll take you home.

840
00:48:58,893 --> 00:49:00,395
Why would you?

841
00:49:01,813 --> 00:49:02,981
You had wine.

842
00:49:03,940 --> 00:49:06,192
You want to be nice to me
after ruining my date?

843
00:49:06,276 --> 00:49:07,777
Just pick a side.

844
00:49:08,111 --> 00:49:09,529
Did I do something wrong?

845
00:49:10,155 --> 00:49:11,948
Tell me. Let me try to understand you.

846
00:49:13,408 --> 00:49:14,451
Well...

847
00:49:17,036 --> 00:49:20,206
You put your hands on your ears.
I thought that was a signal.

848
00:49:20,331 --> 00:49:21,708
Asking for my help.

849
00:49:26,838 --> 00:49:28,882
I'm a joke to you, aren't I?

850
00:49:28,965 --> 00:49:30,216
You think I'm ridiculous.

851
00:49:30,467 --> 00:49:32,010
And that I'm too desperate for love.

852
00:49:32,218 --> 00:49:33,303
It's not like that.

853
00:49:33,887 --> 00:49:36,306
But you know,
I think you're more ridiculous.

854
00:49:36,764 --> 00:49:38,683
You're so ridiculous
that it's not even funny.

855
00:49:41,394 --> 00:49:42,687
You're a lie.

856
00:49:43,480 --> 00:49:45,857
You lied that whole night,
and even your name is a lie.

857
00:49:46,858 --> 00:49:50,236
And you think I'm ridiculous?
That's hilarious to me.

858
00:50:37,867 --> 00:50:39,661
When are you going to stop following me?

859
00:50:39,869 --> 00:50:41,246
Until you're not mad anymore.

860
00:50:42,580 --> 00:50:43,581
What is he saying?

861
00:50:45,416 --> 00:50:46,543
You can go now.

862
00:50:53,091 --> 00:50:54,634
THE SEAGULL

863
00:50:54,717 --> 00:50:55,760
Here.

864
00:50:56,386 --> 00:50:57,387
What's this?

865
00:50:58,179 --> 00:51:00,473
I'm not Lee Jeong-u. I'm Shin Ji-su.

866
00:51:01,558 --> 00:51:04,561
I'm an actor, and I'm 29.

867
00:51:06,187 --> 00:51:09,482
I had to go on that blind date
for someone.

868
00:51:12,318 --> 00:51:13,570
I can't tell you why.

869
00:51:15,113 --> 00:51:16,739
I don't care about your reasons.

870
00:51:17,240 --> 00:51:19,033
That makes no difference to me.

871
00:51:22,078 --> 00:51:23,121
Just take it.

872
00:51:24,247 --> 00:51:25,873
This is like my ID.

873
00:51:26,416 --> 00:51:29,002
I don't want everything about me
to be a lie to you.

874
00:51:33,464 --> 00:51:34,674
THE SEAGULL

875
00:51:34,757 --> 00:51:36,092
I don't understand you.

876
00:51:37,010 --> 00:51:39,804
I don't understand
why you're so desperate to find love.

877
00:51:40,555 --> 00:51:43,391
But I never thought you were ridiculous.

878
00:51:49,564 --> 00:51:51,274
Okay, you can go.

879
00:51:52,150 --> 00:51:53,151
Wait.

880
00:52:14,881 --> 00:52:17,133
What was that just now?

881
00:52:17,592 --> 00:52:21,220
You had something in the back.

882
00:52:26,768 --> 00:52:28,311
Come to the show.

883
00:52:30,521 --> 00:52:31,564
Bye, then.

884
00:53:05,306 --> 00:53:07,892
THE SEAGULL

885
00:53:22,990 --> 00:53:25,743
- Hello?
- Why is it so hard to reach you?

886
00:53:26,744 --> 00:53:27,829
Are you out?

887
00:53:31,040 --> 00:53:32,166
You okay?

888
00:53:32,875 --> 00:53:35,837
I even canceled my class
because you sounded so glum.

889
00:53:36,087 --> 00:53:37,422
No, I'm not okay.

890
00:53:38,631 --> 00:53:41,884
Two men fought because of me.
It was a total mess.

891
00:53:42,927 --> 00:53:44,512
It was terrifying.

892
00:53:45,722 --> 00:53:48,099
How can that happen on a blind date?

893
00:53:48,558 --> 00:53:50,893
You're still pale from panicking.

894
00:53:50,977 --> 00:53:53,730
I told you you'd get a heartburn
if you went too fast.

895
00:53:53,980 --> 00:53:55,606
You need to rest

896
00:53:55,690 --> 00:53:57,650
- after working out...
- Seung-jun said

897
00:53:57,900 --> 00:53:59,944
our bodies needed rest

898
00:54:00,027 --> 00:54:01,529
after overworking them.

899
00:54:01,612 --> 00:54:02,822
You need a break first!

900
00:54:02,905 --> 00:54:05,491
He said that was how you avoided injuries.

901
00:54:06,075 --> 00:54:08,244
And he said the same went for our hearts.

902
00:54:08,327 --> 00:54:10,204
What's the point of telling you, anyway?

903
00:54:21,549 --> 00:54:23,593
LEE HYUN-JU:
ARE YOU STILL INTERESTED IN A BLIND DATE?

904
00:54:27,054 --> 00:54:30,641
So, I decided to take a break
from blind dates.

905
00:54:30,892 --> 00:54:32,435
But I wasn't giving up.

906
00:54:32,769 --> 00:54:36,063
It was a little break
for a stronger takeoff in the future.

907
00:54:38,649 --> 00:54:41,110
Let's go home, girls.

908
00:54:41,819 --> 00:54:42,945
- What?
- Huh?

909
00:54:43,029 --> 00:54:45,323
You've been working so hard
to fill in for me.

910
00:54:45,406 --> 00:54:48,326
Let's have a pampering day. It's on me!

911
00:54:50,203 --> 00:54:51,245
This is embarrassing.

912
00:55:00,338 --> 00:55:01,964
- Is it okay?
- Yeah.

913
00:55:02,423 --> 00:55:03,466
Sae-byeok!

914
00:55:04,091 --> 00:55:05,176
Did it hurt a lot?

915
00:55:05,510 --> 00:55:06,594
Not at all.

916
00:55:08,054 --> 00:55:09,388
Why don't you go first?

917
00:55:09,472 --> 00:55:10,848
You hate your freckles.

918
00:55:10,932 --> 00:55:12,558
Don't you know you need good skincare?

919
00:55:12,642 --> 00:55:14,185
This is super trendy.

920
00:55:14,268 --> 00:55:15,978
But I'm scared.

921
00:55:16,729 --> 00:55:18,773
Come on. Please take good care of her!

922
00:55:32,036 --> 00:55:34,997
That doesn't hurt at all!

923
00:55:36,165 --> 00:55:37,291
No!

924
00:55:39,836 --> 00:55:42,880
Wait! Stop!

925
00:55:42,964 --> 00:55:44,549
- That hurts!
- It's perfect.

926
00:55:47,593 --> 00:55:48,803
This is great.

927
00:55:51,097 --> 00:55:52,265
Did you have a good time?

928
00:55:53,558 --> 00:55:55,560
You're the best, Ui-yeong.

929
00:55:59,105 --> 00:56:02,149
DAD

930
00:56:05,361 --> 00:56:06,696
How are you?

931
00:56:07,113 --> 00:56:09,991
Something reminded me of you at work.
I thought I'd text you.

932
00:56:10,700 --> 00:56:11,868
Take care of your health.

933
00:56:21,043 --> 00:56:24,463
But I still had to straighten things out.

934
00:56:26,465 --> 00:56:29,760
I definitely told him
you didn't want a second date.

935
00:56:30,011 --> 00:56:32,930
And he pretended not to know about that
and asked you out?

936
00:56:34,640 --> 00:56:36,267
It's fine, as long as you told him.

937
00:56:37,602 --> 00:56:39,145
What an odd guy.

938
00:56:39,312 --> 00:56:40,563
Are you okay?

939
00:56:40,646 --> 00:56:42,148
Did you get hurt?

940
00:56:42,231 --> 00:56:45,401
No, he didn't push me.
He pushed the server.

941
00:56:46,027 --> 00:56:48,195
I was a bit scared then, but I'm fine now.

942
00:56:49,363 --> 00:56:50,740
Wait, stay here.

943
00:56:56,245 --> 00:56:58,039
So, did he know or did he not?

944
00:56:59,415 --> 00:57:01,208
You've been friends with him for 20 years!

945
00:57:03,044 --> 00:57:06,047
Don't make me break off our engagement.
Don't mess up.

946
00:57:07,548 --> 00:57:09,508
Ui-yeong told me!

947
00:57:13,596 --> 00:57:14,764
What do you mean?

948
00:57:25,191 --> 00:57:26,692
Are you sure about that?

949
00:57:26,817 --> 00:57:28,444
- Yes, I heard.
- Are you sure?

950
00:57:32,323 --> 00:57:33,658
Where are the representatives?

951
00:57:33,783 --> 00:57:34,951
In the lobby.

952
00:57:35,952 --> 00:57:38,496
- Hello.
- Hi, Ui-yeong, let's talk later.

953
00:57:39,330 --> 00:57:40,456
What's going on?

954
00:57:40,873 --> 00:57:42,083
Ui-yeong!

955
00:57:43,042 --> 00:57:44,251
Did you see this?

956
00:57:45,795 --> 00:57:47,254
THE HILLS HOTEL PREPARES A POP-UP STORE
WITH A PLAGIARIZED DESIGN

957
00:57:47,338 --> 00:57:48,547
"Plagiarized"?

958
00:57:55,513 --> 00:57:58,307
Someone will need to take responsibility
for this!

959
00:57:58,516 --> 00:58:00,101
- I'm so sorry, sir.
- Gosh!

960
00:58:00,309 --> 00:58:01,978
I'll make sure to sort it out!

961
00:58:02,144 --> 00:58:03,312
Sorry, sir!

962
00:58:11,028 --> 00:58:12,446
THE HILLS HOTEL PREPARES A POP-UP STORE
WITH A PLAGIARIZED DESIGN

963
00:58:12,530 --> 00:58:13,823
WILL THIS RUIN THEIR REPUTATION?

964
00:58:14,740 --> 00:58:17,076
How bold of them.

965
00:58:17,493 --> 00:58:19,286
This is last year's work, too.

966
00:58:19,370 --> 00:58:22,248
The Promo Team at the gallery
that worked with Homage reported it.

967
00:58:22,331 --> 00:58:24,166
We said we didn't know

968
00:58:24,250 --> 00:58:26,794
but we won't be completely free
from being held accountable.

969
00:58:27,003 --> 00:58:29,505
Homage has been in a similar situation.

970
00:58:29,672 --> 00:58:31,632
Did Purchasing not do a background check?

971
00:58:32,425 --> 00:58:33,759
Don't tell me you knew it.

972
00:58:33,843 --> 00:58:35,136
How could you think that?

973
00:58:36,303 --> 00:58:37,304
Not at all.

974
00:58:37,847 --> 00:58:40,641
Weren't you supposed to get a proposal
from another company?

975
00:58:40,850 --> 00:58:42,184
They had a great portfolio.

976
00:58:42,309 --> 00:58:44,270
They turned us down.

977
00:58:44,395 --> 00:58:46,230
It seemed to be an internal issue.

978
00:58:46,313 --> 00:58:47,982
We didn't drop them first.

979
00:58:48,149 --> 00:58:51,610
We need to continue with the event,
even if we lose money.

980
00:58:51,736 --> 00:58:55,239
Our reputation will be tanked in no time
if we stop now.

981
00:58:55,656 --> 00:58:58,576
We'll have to compensate Deerfiddich
if they want it.

982
00:58:58,701 --> 00:59:01,370
It'll be better to take the lead
and sort it out now.

983
00:59:01,454 --> 00:59:03,247
Let's do it again, then.

984
00:59:03,330 --> 00:59:05,249
Sales and Marketing,
don't worry about money.

985
00:59:05,332 --> 00:59:06,709
Do whatever Deerfiddich wants.

986
00:59:06,792 --> 00:59:09,628
- Yes, sir.
- Purchasing, find another company.

987
00:59:09,712 --> 00:59:10,713
Absolutely.

988
00:59:10,796 --> 00:59:12,089
Since the schedule's changed

989
00:59:12,214 --> 00:59:14,633
I'll contact the company that dropped out.

990
00:59:24,685 --> 00:59:26,145
How will you...

991
00:59:26,228 --> 00:59:27,271
Hey.

992
00:59:28,355 --> 00:59:30,232
What was that? It was so embarrassing!

993
00:59:31,025 --> 00:59:32,818
- You said you'd take care of it.
- Sorry.

994
00:59:32,902 --> 00:59:34,779
We'll take accountability.

995
00:59:50,961 --> 00:59:52,213
You must've been scared.

996
00:59:53,005 --> 00:59:55,132
Things happen. It's life.

997
00:59:55,216 --> 00:59:57,009
I'll convince HOME to help us out.

998
00:59:57,093 --> 00:59:58,761
Can you give me the CEO's number?

999
01:00:00,221 --> 01:00:02,223
He won't pick up.

1000
01:00:03,307 --> 01:00:05,851
They weren't the ones
who canceled the meeting.

1001
01:00:05,935 --> 01:00:06,977
What?

1002
01:00:08,104 --> 01:00:09,438
I did.

1003
01:00:11,232 --> 01:00:13,734
What do you mean? Why would you do that?

1004
01:00:14,401 --> 01:00:15,820
Ms. Jung told me

1005
01:00:16,570 --> 01:00:18,614
we should only consider Homage.

1006
01:00:18,781 --> 01:00:20,825
She said she'd take care of it

1007
01:00:20,908 --> 01:00:23,911
and told me to cancel the meeting
with HOME.

1008
01:00:24,662 --> 01:00:28,332
- What?
- And Homage copied HOME's work.

1009
01:00:29,542 --> 01:00:30,668
What did you say?

1010
01:00:30,751 --> 01:00:32,878
I'm sorry
for ruining the chance you gave me.

1011
01:00:38,676 --> 01:00:40,136
Everything's been ruined.

1012
01:00:48,978 --> 01:00:50,020
Hello?

1013
01:00:50,479 --> 01:00:52,148
Is this Mr. Lee Eun-ho?

1014
01:00:53,065 --> 01:00:54,191
Yes, that's me.

1015
01:00:54,692 --> 01:00:58,320
Hello, I'm Lee Ui-yeong
from The Hills' Purchasing.

1016
01:00:58,529 --> 01:01:01,949
I tried contacting you,
but couldn't reach you.

1017
01:01:03,242 --> 01:01:04,910
Oh, really?

1018
01:01:05,703 --> 01:01:08,164
You're from The Hills Hotel?

1019
01:01:09,206 --> 01:01:11,292
I just didn't want to talk to you.

1020
01:01:11,375 --> 01:01:13,169
I read the news.

1021
01:01:13,252 --> 01:01:15,588
I was looking forward to seeing
the great design

1022
01:01:15,671 --> 01:01:17,631
that made you cancel our meeting.

1023
01:01:17,715 --> 01:01:19,925
But you just copied our exact design.

1024
01:01:20,050 --> 01:01:21,886
I'm sure you're mad.

1025
01:01:22,136 --> 01:01:25,097
I wanted to talk to you about that.

1026
01:01:25,181 --> 01:01:27,266
Are you at your office right now?

1027
01:01:27,349 --> 01:01:30,060
Don't come. I'm leaving.

1028
01:01:30,144 --> 01:01:32,605
Where are you headed?

1029
01:01:32,688 --> 01:01:34,815
I'll go where you are.

1030
01:01:35,524 --> 01:01:37,693
What if I go really far, huh?

1031
01:01:38,736 --> 01:01:41,906
I'm going to Chuncheon.
You can come if you want.

1032
01:01:42,448 --> 01:01:43,490
- Hey, let's go.
- Hello?

1033
01:01:43,574 --> 01:01:45,534
- Okay, let's go.
- Hello?

1034
01:01:47,161 --> 01:01:49,705
Ridiculous.

1035
01:02:17,775 --> 01:02:20,277
He's definitely inside. He took my call.

1036
01:03:00,234 --> 01:03:01,694
He really left.

1037
01:03:02,695 --> 01:03:04,863
I can't find him
when I don't even know where he is.

1038
01:03:16,709 --> 01:03:19,003
THE SEAGULL

1039
01:03:20,713 --> 01:03:22,006
This is tonight, too.

1040
01:03:36,103 --> 01:03:37,521
Thank you.

1041
01:03:53,495 --> 01:03:57,708
Thank you for coming to our theater.

1042
01:03:57,833 --> 01:03:59,877
The show will begin soon.

1043
01:03:59,960 --> 01:04:01,170
What are you doing?

1044
01:04:01,253 --> 01:04:03,422
You're nervous today.
You're never nervous.

1045
01:04:03,505 --> 01:04:05,215
- Are you waiting for someone?
- Hey!

1046
01:04:05,299 --> 01:04:06,675
It's just a friend.

1047
01:04:06,842 --> 01:04:08,177
- A friend?
- Yeah.

1048
01:04:08,802 --> 01:04:10,095
All food and beverage

1049
01:04:10,179 --> 01:04:13,682
including water, is prohibited.

1050
01:04:13,766 --> 01:04:16,435
Please turn off all your phones

1051
01:04:16,518 --> 01:04:18,312
and other electronics

1052
01:04:18,395 --> 01:04:21,523
for a pleasant experience.

1053
01:04:21,774 --> 01:04:24,818
You may take photos and videos
of the incredible cast

1054
01:04:24,902 --> 01:04:27,363
during the curtain call
after the performance.

1055
01:04:34,661 --> 01:04:36,997
I can't believe I'm actually here.

1056
01:04:38,665 --> 01:04:41,919
And so, this is life.

1057
01:04:43,212 --> 01:04:44,421
And I'm...

1058
01:04:46,215 --> 01:04:47,549
a worker bee.

1059
01:05:05,984 --> 01:05:07,736
Come on!

1060
01:05:08,112 --> 01:05:10,280
That's good.

1061
01:05:10,531 --> 01:05:12,282
- Catch me if you can!
- Watch out!

1062
01:05:12,366 --> 01:05:13,450
Hey!

1063
01:05:20,874 --> 01:05:21,917
Come here!

1064
01:06:44,750 --> 01:06:46,084
Hello?

1065
01:06:47,503 --> 01:06:50,589
I'm Lee Ui-yeong.
We spoke on the phone earlier.

1066
01:06:53,550 --> 01:06:54,676
Hello?

1067
01:06:57,846 --> 01:06:58,972
Mr. Lee?

1068
01:07:09,942 --> 01:07:11,193
Mr. Lee?

1069
01:07:18,200 --> 01:07:19,409
Mr. Lee.

1070
01:07:23,205 --> 01:07:24,206
Mr...

1071
01:07:26,416 --> 01:07:28,001
Oh, gosh, I'm so sorry!

1072
01:07:29,753 --> 01:07:30,754
Oh...

1073
01:07:31,463 --> 01:07:33,840
I'm sorry! My phone!

1074
01:07:38,178 --> 01:07:39,304
Tae-seop!

1075
01:07:40,222 --> 01:07:41,723
What are you doing here?

1076
01:07:45,352 --> 01:07:46,353
Ui-yeong?

1077
01:07:46,895 --> 01:07:48,397
Are you here to see me?

1078
01:07:48,480 --> 01:07:50,274
What? Me?

1079
01:07:50,357 --> 01:07:52,192
No, I'm here for work.

1080
01:07:55,362 --> 01:07:57,239
Are you...

1081
01:07:58,115 --> 01:08:00,409
- I'm the CEO of HOME.
- Oh, I see.

1082
01:08:00,742 --> 01:08:02,369
You're the CEO of HOME...

1083
01:08:02,953 --> 01:08:03,954
What?

1084
01:08:09,710 --> 01:08:12,588
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

1085
01:08:18,218 --> 01:08:19,970
A 1% CHANCE? STILL A CHANCE

1086
01:08:21,597 --> 01:08:23,432
TODAY'S TO DO: GO ON A BLIND DATE
TOMORROW'S TO DO: GO ON A BLIND DATE

1087
01:08:25,309 --> 01:08:27,853
THAT'S THE END OF US. THE END!

1088
01:08:28,937 --> 01:08:31,356
UI-YEONG! SEOLTANG!

1089
01:08:35,193 --> 01:08:37,613
I DON'T WANT EVERYTHING ABOUT ME
TO BE A LIE TO YOU

1090
01:08:45,245 --> 01:08:46,663
What brings you here?

1091
01:08:46,747 --> 01:08:47,914
Oh, a shooting star!

1092
01:08:47,998 --> 01:08:49,249
Make a wish! Quick!

1093
01:08:49,416 --> 01:08:52,002
Let's invite her to stay the night here
if she's okay.

1094
01:08:54,588 --> 01:08:57,090
I was waiting for you,
thinking you might come late.

1095
01:08:57,174 --> 01:08:58,175
What about tomorrow evening?

1096
01:08:58,258 --> 01:08:59,259
Ui-yeong.

1097
01:09:00,844 --> 01:09:02,971
Since it's a basketball cartoon,
how about a basketball game?

1098
01:09:03,055 --> 01:09:04,431
If I beat you...

1099
01:09:05,641 --> 01:09:07,851
You're not here to apologize.
Tell me the truth.

1100
01:09:08,018 --> 01:09:09,144
It's pouring outside!

1101
01:09:09,227 --> 01:09:10,270
Ui-yeong!

1102
01:09:10,562 --> 01:09:11,772
How would you like me

1103
01:09:12,481 --> 01:09:14,149
to remember you?

1104
01:09:20,072 --> 01:09:22,074
Subtitles by: Min-sun Kim
